race.comment: Tough. WIMMERA STAR (4) peaks off a 1L defeat at Horsham over 1800m. Raced favourite in that and looks well enough placed to go one better. COUSINS DAY (5) was in the firing line on the bend and held on to place over 2000m at this track, beaten 2.75 lengths. Keeps Yendall and will take pegging back with the extra fitness. SQUANDER (13) missed a whisker at both Hamilton at Ararat before delivering a CL1 at Mt Gambier at a short quote. Has an awkward gate but is a chance to go on. ADMIRE ACE (2) draws wide but is worth another chance over this trip. His Maiden win over a mile at Kilmore two back hinted at better things to come. If we forgive the latest, THE KINGS GOSPEL (10) should be around the mark.
